chio-replay-gate test signing seed
==================================

WARNING: NON-PRODUCTION TEST KEY MATERIAL.

This file (`test-key.seed`) holds the 32 raw bytes of an Ed25519 signing
seed used exclusively by the M04 deterministic-replay gate. It is NOT a
secret and MUST NOT be reused for any production credential, capability
issuer, or signing role.

Derivation
----------

The seed is the SHA-256 digest of the literal ASCII byte string:

    chio-replay-gate-non-production-test-seed-v1

In Python (reference):

    import hashlib
    seed = hashlib.sha256(
        b"chio-replay-gate-non-production-test-seed-v1"
    ).digest()
    assert len(seed) == 32

This "nothing-up-my-sleeve" derivation lets any reviewer recompute the
seed bytes from a single short ASCII string, so the test material has no
hidden provenance.

Hex (lowercase, no separators):

    1335337915b7d8b81391fa776eee31a5808cbab959aa3dcc91f93049cbf4fd44

Loader contract
---------------

`ScenarioDriver::new` (in `tests/replay/src/driver.rs`) reads
`tests/replay/test-key.seed`, asserts the file is exactly 32 bytes, and
constructs an `ed25519_dalek::SigningKey` via
`SigningKey::from_bytes(&seed)`. The driver then uses that signing key
together with a fixed clock and a deterministic nonce counter so that
replayed receipts are byte-identical across machines and OSes.

Integrity
---------

`test-key.seed.sha256` holds the lowercase hex SHA-256 of `test-key.seed`
on a single line with no trailing newline:

    b32580c7001b8ad7cc9d29d4f8d4faf2ad067db558add9bb7e02bf8f5f9a01af

Future replay-gate CI lanes can reverify the seed by comparing
`sha256(test-key.seed)` against the hex stored in
`test-key.seed.sha256`. Any drift indicates either tampering or an
accidental edit and MUST fail the gate.

Do not reuse
------------

This signing seed is checked into source. Treat it like any other test
fixture: do NOT issue real credentials with it, do NOT import it into a
production HSM or KMS, and do NOT include the resulting verifying key in
a production trust root.
